## Minimal workflow demonstrating an inline `supervisor` declaration.
## The watchdog supervises the `implement` agent node concurrently and
## enqueues steering messages it picks up at its next turn — scoped to
## that node. See docs/supervisors.md.

supervisor watchdog:
  watches: [implement]
  model: "anthropic/claude-opus-4-8"
  system: watchdog_policy
  cooldown: "30s"
  max_evals: 15

prompt watchdog_policy:
  You watch an implementer agent. Stay silent while it makes steady
  progress. Intervene (one short, actionable message) only if you see it
  edit files outside src/, repeat a failing Bash command without changing
  approach, or drift from the stated task. Register a tool_error monitor
  on Bash so you are woken immediately when a command fails.

prompt task:
  Implement the requested change with tests.

agent implement:
  model: "anthropic/claude-opus-4-8"
  system: task

workflow main:
  entry: implement
  implement -> done
